Anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The Leoben Branch of the Communist Party of Austria and the Donawitz Iron Works in Austria and Contea and Coba farms in Guinea held a meeting, film show, lecture and photo exhibition on July 1 and 2 on the occasion of the 8th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise.
 The chairman of the Leoben Branch of the party, the younger brother of the Guinean President and other figures made speeches at the functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers said the three principles of national reunification, 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo put forward by the president are the fairest and most reasonable offers for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il formulated the proposals for reunification set forth by the president as the three charters for national reunification and has wisely led the cause of national reunification true to the behest of the president, thus achieving shining successes, they said.

Kim Yong Nam pays courtesy call on Indonesian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Jakarta, July 11 (KCNA correspondent) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, paid a courtesy call on Indonesian President Megawati Soekarnoputri on July 11.
 At the meeting Kim Yong Nam conveyed warm greetings from General Secretary Kim Jong Il to the Indonesian President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing deep thanks for them, the Indonesian President asked Kim Yong Nam to transmit her sincere regards to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were Paek Nam Sun, foreign minister, Ri Kwang Gun, Minister of Foreign Trade, Jang Chang Chon, DPRK Ambassador to Indonesia, and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there from the Indonesian side were Taufiq Kiemas, husband of the Indonesian President, Nur Hassan Wirayuda, Foreign Minister, Syamsul Muarif, Minister of State for Communications and Information, Bambang Kesowo, secretary of state and cabinet, and other officials concerned.

Sculpture "Recollection of White Horse" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- "I'd like to rephrase the phraseology 'a loyal dog and a lovable horse' as 'a loyal horse and a lovable dog'. Whenever I retrospect my days in Wangqing, I always remember the legendary white horse with which I went through the flames of the anti-Japanese war."
 This is what President Kim Il Sung says in his reminiscences "With the Century" vol. 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A marble sculpture "Recollection of the White Horse" is on display in the gift exhibition of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sculpture has the horse at its center with the president's satchel and coat on its saddle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It vividly shows the horse waiting for the president, who went somewhere a few minutes ago, leaving a book and pencil on a stump on which he had sat, making a blueprint for national liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mane and tail of the horse blowing in the soft breeze well represent the characteristics of the horse loyal to its master. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delicate and soft color of the marble to which the method of touch was applied brings into bolder relief the characteristics of the clever horse trying not to disturb the president in thinking. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The marble of white color is 97 cm90 cm.

Hard-fought battle during Korean War 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- There was a battle on Height 351 in the last period of the Korean War.
 The height is located in the southeastern part of Kosong county, Kangwon Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After occupying the height, a tactical vantage in the eastern sector of the front in 1951 the U.S. imperialists made desperate efforts to use it as a stronghold to break through the flank of the KPA front and penetrate deep into the north by joining their units landing on the east coast. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Taking advantage of this height the enemy conducted most frantic military operations including reconnaissance and naval bombardment on the depth of the tactical defence theatre of the KPA unit, actions to threaten the flank of the KPA forces and obstruction to the transport of military supplies to the eastern sector of the front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After building strong defences on the height for over two years, the enemy forces said that they should not yield Height 351 to the KPA even if they would abandon Seoul." And they described the height as an "invulnerable fortress" and "line of no retreat". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tasked to occupy and defend the height, a KPA unit seized it in just 15 minutes after it mounted a fierce attack under the cover of strong artillery fire at the night of June 2, Juche 42 (1953). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its combatants honorably defended the height by beating back the enemy's persistent counter-attacks for nearly 50 days. 
 In this period they killed or wounded 8,500 troops and destroyed or captured lots of combat equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The title of the DPRK Hero was awarded to 14 servicemen including Kim In Thaek, Kim Ryong Thaek and Ju Sang Ha who silenced the enemy's machine-guns with their bodies to make a breakthrough in the unit's charge.

Kim Yong Nam meets senior officials of Indonesia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jakarta, July 11 (KCNA correspondent)- Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly conversation with Indonesian vice-president Hamzah Haz who paid a courtesy call on him on July 11.
 Present there were DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, DPRK Ambassador to Indonesia Jang Chang Chon and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Indonesian Foreign Minister Nur Hassan Wirayuda, Minster of State for Communications and Information Syamsul Muarif and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Kim Yong Nam had a talk with Amien Rais, speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly of Indonesia, on the same day.

Agreements signed between DPRK and Indonesia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jakarta, July 11 (KCNA correspondent) -- An agreement on preventing double taxation and tax evasion on income and an agreement on scientific and technological cooperation were signed between the governments of the DPRK and Indonesia in Jakarta on July 11.
 Present at the signing ceremonies from the DPRK side were president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Kim Yong Nam, Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Kwang Gun, president of the Academy of Sciences Ri Kwang Ho, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, DPRK Ambassador to Indonesia Jang Chang Chon and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present from the Indonesian side were Indonesian President Megawati Soekarnoputri, Foreign Minister Nur Hassan Wirayuda, Minister of Industry and Trade Rini Mariani Soewandi, Minister of State for Research, Sciences and Technology Hatta Rajasa, Minister of State for Culture and Tourism I. Gde Ardhika and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agreements were signed by DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun and president of the Academy of Sciences Ri Kwang Ho, authorized by the DPRK government, and by Indonesian Foreign Minister Nur Hassan Wirayuda and Minister of State for Research, Sciences and Technology Hatta Rajasa, authorized by the Indonesian government.

Talks held between Kim Yong Nam and Indonesian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jakarta, July 11 (KCNA correspondent) -- Talks between Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and Megawati Soekarnoputri, Indonesian President, were held in Jakarta on July 11.
 Present there from the DPRK side were Paek Nam Sun, Foreign Minister, Ri Kwang Gun, Minister of Foreign Trade, Ri Kwang Ho, president of the Academy of Sciences, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Jang Chang Chon, DPRK Ambassador to Indonesia, and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present from the Indonesian side were Nur Hassan Wirayuda, Foreign Minister, Rini Mariani Soewandi, Minister of Industry and Trade, Hatta Rajasa, Minister of State for Research, Sciences and Technology, I. Gde Ardhika, Minister of State for Culture and Tourism, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged their views on the issue of boosting the DPRK-Indonesia friendly relations based on the special friendship that existed between President Kim Il Sung and former Indonesian President Soekarno in the new century and issues of mutual concern and reached a consensus of views on the matters discussed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK side referred to the great successes made by it in the building of a powerful nation, the efforts for national reunification and foreign relations under the army-based leadership of Kim Jong Il and underscored the need to reinforce the friendly and cooperative ties between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Indonesian side underlined the importance of strengthening the mutual support and cooperation on the international arena including the non-aligned movement and appreciated the Korean people's efforts to achieve the reunification of Korea through dialogue and negotiations.

City visited by many Koreans and foreigners
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Kaesong, a city near the Military Demarcation Line in Korea, attracts the world's attention because of truce village Panmunjom.
 It is visited by many Koreans from all walks of life and foreigners on the occasion of the Day of Victory in the War (July 27). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are in Panmunjom the halls where the armistice talks were held and the Armistice Agreement was signed and the room where the military armistice commission met. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From there one can see the concrete wall dividing Korea into the north and south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Korean military dictators built this wall in the area south of the MDL. It extends over 240 km from the west to the east. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wall bisects 8 counties, 122 villages, 3 railways, highways and more than 220 roads, big and small, between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wall shows who truly wants peace and reunification and who seeks war and division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kaesong, which was the capital city of Koryo, has many scenic spots and historic sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mt. Songak covered with pine trees and round rocks and Pakyon Falls, one of the three famous falls in Korea, and historical remains there present spectacular scenery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are in the city at least 100 historic sites dating back to the Koryo dynasty including the Koryo Songgyungwan Academy with a history of over 1,000 years, the south gate, the Sonjuk Bridge, the Manwol Pavilion and Anhwa Temple. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mausoleums of kings Wang Kon and Kong Min are a clear reminder of the nation's excellent architecture in building tombs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also a producer of famous Koryo Insam (ginseng).

Kim Il Sung's reminiscences published in Austria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Vol. 4 of part 1- the anti-Japanese revolution of President Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century" was published by the Josef Gebauer Publishing House in Austria on July 5.
 The publishing house in a preface of the reminiscences said that the Korean people experienced unprecedented ordeals and crisis after the demise of Kim Il Sung, adding that over the last 8 years they have emerged victorious thanks to his idea and will under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, true to the behest of the president. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The life of the president was one of a great revolutionary, a great man who devoted his all to the people, always mixing with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was his maxim that people are always his teacher and everything should be done for their sake. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president regarded the people as his teacher all his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He placed their interests above all in shaping line and policies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He always mixed with them to meet their wishes and interests and shared weal and woe with them, thus leading the revolution and construction to victory.

Kim Yong Nam feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Jakarta, July 11, (KCNA correspondent) -- Indonesian President Megawati Soekarnoputri hosted a banquet in the presidential palace this evening in honor of Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and his party on an official goodwill visit to Indonesia.
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Nam, Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Kwang Gun, president of the Academy of Sciences Ri Kwang Ho, acting chairman of the Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, DPRK Ambassador to Indonesia Jang Chang Chon and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banquet was attended by Megawati Soekarnoputri and her husband Taufiq Kiemas, speaker of the House of Representatives Akbar Tandjung, chairman of the Supreme Advisory Council Achmad Tirtosudiro, Foreign Minister Nur Hassan Wirayuda and other ministers, commanders of the armed forces and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Megawati in a speech warmly welcomed Kim Yong Nam and his party, saying that the current visit of the president firmly convinced her of the close relations of friendship and cooperation between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the governments and the peoples of Indonesia and the DPRK have closely cooperated with each other in bilateral and multilateral relations and on the international arenas including the non-aligned movement, she expressed her belief that if the peoples of the two countries pool their efforts they can accomplish many things. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Extending full support to the Korean people in their struggle to ensure security and stability on the Korean Peninsula, she expressed her expectation that the DPRK would take an active part in the ASEAN regional forum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam in a speech said that he is greatly rejoiced over the fact that the DPRK-Indonesia friendship based on special friendship that existed between President Kim Il Sung and President Sukarno are favorably developing generation after generation. He expressed the conviction that the current visit would offer one more important opportunity of giving an impetus to steadily boosting the bilateral relations provided by the preceding leaders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, he noted, are rejoiced over big progress made by the Indonesian government and people in their efforts to achieve social stability and economic recovery. He extended full support and solidarity to their efforts to defend national sovereignty and territorial integrity and raise the international prestige of Indonesia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that it is the consistent stand of the DPRK to expand and develop the long-standing friendship with Indonesia in all fields, Kim Yong Nam declared that the DPRK would continue to favorably develop the bilateral relations so as to meet the expectations of the two peoples and the requirements of the new century and make a positive contribution to regional peace, progress and prosperity.

U.S. brasshat's crafty artifice refuted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The commander of the U.S. Forces in South Korea was reported to have issued what he called "statement" as regards the incident in which two girl students were driven over to death by an armored car of the U.S. troops. 
This is nothing but a crafty artifice to calm down the anti-U.S. sentiment mounting high in its wake and evade the responsibility for it. Minju Joson today says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As soon as the two girl students were killed by the armored car in Yangju county, Kyonggi Province in broad daylight on June 13, the U.S. Forces side was busy with moves to hide the truth of the incident and flee from the responsibility for it from the outset and had no idea of making any "apology" for what happened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When a strong campaign was launched in different parts of South Korea to demand a probe into the truth of the incident and the punishment of those responsible for the crime, the U.S. Forces side made much fuss, belatedly "indicting the driver of the armoured car" and "releasing a statement". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialists truly feel responsible for the crime, how can they organize a celebration of their independence day with such pomp and splendour, turning a deaf ear to the demands of the families of those killed and other South Koreans for reparation and how can they unilaterally refuse to let the criminals face prosecution though nearly one month has passed since the occurrence of the incident or allow them to freely go to the bar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This fact once again reveals how brazen-faced and crafty the U.S. imperialists are. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There should be neither concession nor compromise in the struggle against the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that a similar tragedy is bound to occur again as long as they are allowed to stay in South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists should take an honest and responsible attitude towards the probe into the incident and reparation for the killing and immediately pull their aggressor forces out of South Korea.
